shearing blast
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:Shearing-blast may be of two kinds. True shearing-blast is caused by the comb of the shearing-machine actually damaging the surface of the skin. This defect is seen as numerous lines parallel to each other running in various directions on the skin. The other defect [in pelts] often described as shearing-blast is really due to sunburn.
